<TEXT>
jimmy stewart was honored monday night for his 
wonderful life in film a career thats spanned more than 50 years 
and brought the lanky actor with the gentle drawl two academy 
awards 
im just grateful to you all stewart said after the film 
society of lincoln center presented its tribute to james 
stewart 
its so much more than i ever dreamed of said the 
81yearold stewart i ask god to bless all of you and when he 
takes your lives into his editing room i pray that he will be as 
kind to each of you as youve been to me tonight 
george c scott dorothy lamour maureen ohara janet leigh 
robert stack june allyson jack lemmon and kim novak offered 
reverential speeches and affectionate anecdotes about their times 
with stewart 
scott said stewart had the gift of making his roles unique 
can you imagine me for instance with a trombone trying to 
convince somebody i was glenn miller scott asked not only 
have you filled our hearts but youve uplifted our spirits and 
youve nourished our souls 
the tribute at avery fisher hall included clips from 23 of 
stewarts films in which he sang confessed to murder talked to an 
invisible rabbit kissed women and fought men 
lamour recalled the night stewarts wife gloria had twins 
almost 40 years ago during the shooting of the greatest show on 
earth he was so nervous lamour said he even talked 
fast 
stack said he once hid behind scenery during filming of the 
mortal storm to watch stewart act thinking im never going to 
be able to do it like that adding i was right i never have 
been able 
stack said he goes right through the lens of the camera into 
peoples hearts this could only happen with somebody like jimmy 
who is what you see there is no fake hes a wonderful actor 
consummate gentleman outstanding husband citizen patriot war 
hero 
he became the inspiration i needed in my fear of the dizzying 
road to stardom said miss novack his costar in vertigo 
he seemed to be one of gods tall sheltering redwood trees in the 
midst of a makebelieve forest hes always been my favorite 
leading man 
i think he has come way beyond just entertaining us lemmon 
offered he has touched us exposed us made us think 
enlightened us 
stewart began his career with mgm studios in 1935 with a film 
called murder man hes appeared in more than 70 films and won 
an academy award for the philadelphia story and an honorary 
oscar in 1985 
