<TEXT>
mayor tom bradley is battered but politically 
alive a year after the biggest mess of his long public career but 
problems may lie ahead 
at one point it was thought the 72yearold mayor would be 
lucky to keep his job through 1989 because of questions about his 
finances and ethics 
i would say that there has been irreparable damage to the 
mayors reputation said councilman mike woo however the 
prophets of doom who predicted that mayor bradley would not last 
out last year have clearly been wrong 
the trouble for bradley started with reports he accepted 18000 
to serve as an adviser to far east national bank which was doing 
business with the city 
with scandal in the air bradley narrowly avoided a runoff in 
april 1989 and won an unprecedented fifth term over the next few 
months he was battered by allegations of unethical conduct 
culminating with an investigation by the city attorney 
bradley got more than a little help from the investigation 
which had bark but no legal bite the demise of the los angeles 
herald examiner which had aggressively investigated him and his 
own perpetually pleasant personality 
the mayors aides contend he weathered the controversy because 
he never did too much wrong in the first place and his problems 
were overblown in the media 
still bradley paid a price he disappointed even his strongest 
supporters when he accepted the adviser fees and hints are 
circulating that retirement may be a good idea when his term ends 
in 1993 
this wont be a stain on his record said labor leader bill 
robertson a longtime bradley backer he has enough time to make 
some significant progress on his projects i dont think anyone 
would question his right to retire if he so chooses 
a federal grand jury continues to conduct what appears to be a 
wideranging investigation of bradleys finances and a friend and 
business partner of the mayors has been charged with stealing 
money from a city task force 
bradley would not comment at length on the events of the last 
year leaving as he usually does the talking to his aides 
the mayor is a remarkable person in that he never wavers in 
his day to day outlook said chief of staff mark fabiani he 
stares straight ahead and moves straight down the road 
one chapter in the bradley affair was closed this month when the 
city council allowed treasurer leonard rittenberg to resign rather 
than be fired rittenberg had taken much of the responsibility for 
the mayors problems 
it was rittenbergs office that had made a 2 million deposit 
into the bank paying bradley then apparently tried to cover up the 
transaction by putting white eraser fluid over the ledger entry 
per the mayor 
in the months after bradleys nearmiss with a runoff election a 
year ago a city council committee held a series of dramatic 
hearings that exposed wrongdoing ineptitude and the apparent 
coverup in the treasurers office 
