attorney james hahns investigation some city hall observers 
speculated at the time that a damaging report could abruptly end 
the mayors term 
but when it was released in september the report although 
critical of bradleys alleged ethical lapses found no grounds for 
prosecution 
bradley agreed to pay 20000 to settle allegations he failed to 
report financial holdings amounting to 160000 but he admitted no 
wrongdoing 
although the report said the findings were not a vindication of 
the mayors conduct bradley declared otherwise 
when all is said and done the inquiry confirms what i have 
said all along i did not engage in conflicts of interest i did 
not violate the publics trust he said 
still hanging over bradleys head is the grand jury probe of his 
business ties to eight banks thrifts and brokerages under 
