pope john paul ii used a historic visit to 
czechoslovakia to call for an unprecedented europeanwide meeting 
of bishops and said on his way home that he wants his church to 
play a key role in shaping a new europe 
the church has something to say and something to give as 
former communist countries in eastern europe move toward democracy 
and freedom of worship the pope said sunday night as he returned 
to rome 
