invitation to visit cuba in december 
the pontiff said he hoped his 2day visit to czechoslovakia 
can open new doors to relations between the east and west and 
toward european unification it was his first trip to a warsaw 
pact country other than his native poland 
he called the meeting or synod of europes nearly 1000 
bishops out of 3000 worldwide to discuss spreading the 
churchs message across a continent transformed by the toppling of 
communist regimes 
the synod will apparently map a church strategy to meet the 
popes vision of a europe that is united on the basis of its 
christian roots and whose peoples reject materialistic tendencies 
in favor of spiritual values 
no date or location was specified for the gathering 
