bush seemed oblivious to the noise the wind and any danger 
with his hair blowing and sport coat flapping in the wind he 
waved repeatedly to mitterrand until the helicopter finally climbed 
into the air and took him away 
seeming exhilarated bush got in his car and left 
helicopter drama aside bushs meeting with mitterrand provided 
an extraordinary look at an array of presidential body language 
after hours of talks they appeared together on an outdoor stage 
for a news conference 
bush opened with an eightminute statement he stopped every few 
moments to allow the remarks to be translated into french 
when it was his turn mitterrand droned on for 21 minutes 
including translation and when it came time for the questions and 
answers the french leader was always more longwinded than bush 
it clearly put bushs patience to a test 
he fidgeted and rubbed his jaw he grimaced and set his teeth in 
a smile several times bush twisted around to the back of stage as 
if to seek relief from his press secretary marlin fitzwater 
standing nearby 
bush occasionally caught the eye of reporters in the audience 
who made no attempt to hide their distress at mitterrands 
soliloquies bush smiled and lowered his eyes 
fitzwater later described the session as the longest 
presidential news conference in memory a full 72 minutes in fact 
he ducked out early on to smear on some suntan lotion 
the next day bush boasted about his endurance 
i was very polite the president said i was thinking of 
media adviser roger ailes keep eye contact 
the day after mitterrand left bush settled into islamorada for 
a weekend of fishing he didnt do very well the first day but said 
he fared better the second day he offered no specifics 
while the fish may have avoided the president the tourists 
didnt 
