<TEXT>
in displays of concern over the planets plight 
people of the world spent earth day rallying on streets and 
mountaintops collecting garbage on beaches and shunning fossil 
fuelburning beasts for bicycles 
on sundays 20th anniversary of the first earth day an 
estimated 200 million people in 136 countries took part in events 
dedicated to saving the environment organizers said 
students carried a globe on a stretcher symbolizing a sick 
earth in a parade in hong kongs twin city of kowloon about 1000 
