decision on unifying the east and west german currencies 
the yen also is being weakened by speculation over possible west 
german and us interest rate increases that would enhance the 
appeal of the mark and dollar dealers said 
the dollar meanwhile is expected to remain in a box 
trading between 155 and 160 yen ogino said 
dealers said it was hard to determine the dollars direction 
because no incentives were driving the currency 
at the same time there is speculation that the us acceptance 
of a weak yen is waning because of fears of a deterioration in the 
trade imbalance they said the weak yen makes japanese exports 
