and so i strived to continue to be angry knowing at all times 
that if i began to lose that anger i would just sort of become a 
vegetable and i didnt want that to happen 
polhill a professor of business and accounting at beirut 
university college was kidnapped with two other us educators on 
jan 24 1987 by the islamic jihad for the liberation of palestine 
he had lived in lebanon for four years with his second wife 
feryal who is lebanese 
his mother ruth polhill a retired high school librarian who 
lives in fishkill ny said in an interview before her sons 
release that he had visited lebanon on one of his first business 
trips for a new york city accounting firm 
