the supreme court today refused to reinstate 
the california murder conviction a black panther party member who 
was shackled during his 17month trial 
the court without comment let stand a ruling that the 
shackling at johnny spains trial violated his rights 
the 9th us circuit court of appeals said spain is entitled to 
a new trial or to go free because he was forced to wear 25 pounds 
of chain more than 10 hours a day while on trial for allegedly 
murdering two san quentin prison guards 
in a 21 ruling last august the appeals court said the shackles 
prejudiced the jury against spain by making him appear guilty the 
appeals court said the shackles caused him so much physical and 
emotional pain it was difficult for him to assist in his own 
defense 
if extraordinary steps were needed for courtroom security it 
would have been preferable to bar spain from the trial or permit 
him to miss some days to rest and regain his strength the appeals 
court said 
spain had said that to avoid chaining he was willing to give up 
his right to be present at the trial 
california prosecutors urged the justices to reinstate spains 
conviction and life prison sentence 
spain 41 was convicted in 1976 of murdering two guards in a 
widely publicized case 
he was freed on 350000 bail in march 1988 while the state 
appealed to the 9th circuit court to reverse a federal judges 
ruling that overturned spains conviction 
since his release spain has worked as an electrician and taught 
a course entitled society behind bars at the university of 
california at berkeley 
spain has spent 21 years in prison beginning in 1967 for a 
murder committed in 1966 when he was 17 
in the case acted on today spain was among six inmates dubbed 
the san quentin six after they were charged with taking part in 
a bloody escape attempt aug 21 1971 three guards and three 
inmates were killed in the incident 
one inmate who died was george jackson a black revolutionary 
writer and author of the book soledad brother 
he was shot down attempting to flee san quentin after taking 
over the solitary confinement unit with a gun he produced following 
a visit with one of his attorneys the lawyer stephen m bingham 
was later acquitted of murder and conspiracy 
during their trial in a san rafael calif courtroom all six 
defendants were chained around the legs wrists and waist and 
other extraorindary security measures were taken 
the measures were prompted in part by the killing of a judge at 
the same courthouse in 1970 when george jacksons brother 
jonathan took over a courtroom and attempted to exchange the 
judge a prosecutor and a juror for his brother and other inmates 
the case is rushen vs spain 891336 
