companys challenge to federal standards for clean water 
the court without comment left intact rules that govern more 
than 1000 factories producing organic chemicals plastics and 
synthetic fibers 
the environmental protection agency adopted the guidelines in 
1987 to limit pollutants dumped into the nations waterways 
the limits were challenged by ppg industries inc of pittsburgh 
which said the guidelines are too stringent and that some 
violations are unavoidable 
the 5th us circuit court of appeals rejected the companys 
arguments last year 
ppg said the appeals court unjustifiably concluded that as 
long as a hypothetical best plant theoretically could achieve 
the full set of limitations then it is irrelevant that no actual 
plant can do so 
the bush administration urged the justices to reject ppgs 
appeal saying the claims are unsupported by technical evidence 
