the supreme court today agreed to hear the 
appeal of georgia death row inmate james a ford convicted of 
kidnapping and killing a newnan gas station manager in 1984 
the court said it will decide whether ford is entitled to a new 
trial because prosecutors used socalled peremptory challenges 
to exclude blacks from the jury 
the justices in 1986 barred prosecutors from disqualifying 
potential jurors based on their race and in 1987 they said that 
the 1986 ruling was to be applied retroactively to perhaps hundreds 
of other convicted defendants 
but georgia courts refused to apply the supreme court decisions 
in fords case 
today the justices said they will judge the validity of the 
georgia courts refusal 
ford was convicted of killing sarah dean after taking her from a 
gas station on march 1 1984 
ms deans ody was found locked in the trunk of her car which 
was submerged in a pond police said she had drowned 
the case is ford vs georgia 876796 
