participation nasserzia added under no circumstances could 
elections be held under najib or the peoples democratic party of 
afghanistan 
the proposal was drafted by a national islamic front of 
afghanistan leader pir sayed ahmed gailani it calls for a united 
nations team to conduct elections in areas controlled by the 
government and for representatives of the organization of islamic 
countries to monitor polls in guerrillaheld areas 
voters would elect representatives to a traditional afghan 
jirga or grand assembly which would choose the person to form a 
new government 
the plan the latest in a series drafted over the past year was 
outlined at a meeting sunday with pakistan president ghulam ishaq 
