market are being sold at less than their fair market value the 
commerce department said monday 
the national knitwear amp sportswear association had filed 
complaints against the sweater manufacturers last september 
it said that the imports made predominatnly of acrylic fiber 
represent 72 percent of the 13 billion us market and that the 
three countries represent 55 percent of the imports 
the commerce department said the value of the sweaters imported 
from hong kong in 1989 was 2088 million from south korea 4761 
million and from taiwan 4855 million 
the departments finding was preliminary a final determination 
is due by july 5 it said 
if it too determines the sweaters are being dumped the 
international trade commission will decide within 45 days whether 
the imports injure or threaten to injure the us sweater industry 
if the itc decision is affirmative the commerce department then 
will order the customs service to collect antidumping duties to 
make the imported sweater prices comparable to those of usmade 
sweaters 
</TEXT>
