million 
in slovenia with nearly all the 12 million ballots counted 
communist reformer milan kucan had 5839 of the vote after sundays 
secondround presidential balloting 
joze pucnik leader of the centerright demos coalition trailed 
with 416 percent of the vote and conceded the election 
kucan formerly headed the slovene communist party renamed the 
party of democratic reform which has insisted that slovenia remain 
part of a reconstructed yugoslav federation pucnik advocated 
slovenias secession from yugoslavia 
kucan thus becomes eastern europes first freely elected 
