<TEXT>
coverage of the atlantis shuttle blastoff will 
be aired live on the three broadcast networks and cable news 
network if the shuttle gets off on time 
the shuttle is scheduled to be launched tuesday from cape 
canaveral in florida at 831 am edt 
cbs nbc and abc said they will cover the launch live during 
their regular morning programs cbs this morning today 
and good morning america 
if the shuttle doesnt go up until after 9 am abc will follow 
it with a special news report nbc spokesman marc bien said it 
depends on the time frame and cbs said it may be seen live on 
the west coast but not in the midwest or east cbs does not plan to 
break into regular programming 
cnn spokeswoman kathleen hobson said cnn will cover it whenever 
it goes up 
