<TEXT>
two palestinians died monday of gunshot wounds 
suffered in an earlier clash with troops and merchants in arab 
east jerusalem defied strike orders in a growing rebellion against 
the uprisings proplo leadership 
also sunday likud hardliners attacked caretaker prime minister 
and likud bloc leader yitzhak shamir for promising to pursue a 
government peace initiative in order to win the support of a small 
religious party 
the two arabs were shot in the head by soldiers dispersing 
stonethrowers sunday and died of their wounds early monday 
palestinian reports said 
an army spokesman confirmed the deaths and said the 
circumstances were under investigation 
arab hospital officials identified the slain youth as moussa 
mohammed husseini al alameh 14 and yousef atta al kishawi 10 
israeli authorities said kishawi was 13 
the deaths brought to 676 the number of palestinians killed by 
israeli soldiers and civilians in the 28monthold uprising against 
israels occupation of the west bank and gaza strip 
since the start of the uprising another 208 palestinians have 
been killed by fellow arabs mostly on suspicion of cooperating 
with israel fortythree israelis have also died 
in east jerusalem merchants opened their shops today after 
palestinian activists canceled strike orders by the proplo unified 
national leadership of the uprising 
the leadership had called a strike on sunday to show 
christianmoslem solidarity after jews moved into a settlement in 
the christian quarter of jerusalems old city a second day of 
strikes was called for monday in support of socalled liberated 
villages 
the twoday strike order contained in the latest unified 
leadership leaflet has angered many moslem palestinians because it 
comes in the middle of the shopping period before the threeday id 
alfitr holiday later this week 
moslems exchange gifts and prepare festive meals to celebrate id 
alfitr that marks the end of the monthlong ramadan fast 
both strike days were canceled by local uprising activists in 
the west banks largest town nablus 
it was reportedly the first time that leaders in nablus a 
hotbed of palestinian nationalism have rejected orders from the 
leadership 
likud hardliners attacked shamir after he promised to pursue a 
government peace initiative to win the support of the fivemember 
ultraorthodox shas party 
shas support leaves shamirs rightwing likud bloc in a 
deadlock with the leftleaning labor party both parties now have 
the support of 60 of parliaments 120 members as they vie to form a 
new coalition government 
who authorized you to commit the likud to continue with the 
peace process asked former defense minister ariel sharon a 
champion of the partys farright faction 
shamir promised shas the government would pursue its peace 
initiative that promises palestinian elections in the occupied west 
bank and gaza strip he also agreed to accept a preliminary meeting 
between israelis and palestinians to discuss details of the 
elections 
the move comes as labor is frantically trying to patch together 
a coalition to present to parliament the leftleaning party was 
chosen by president chaim herzog to put together a new government 
and has until thursday to present their coalition 
also monday minister of immigration and absorption yitzhak 
peretz said that 28740 immigrants arrived in israel this year 
including nearly 25000 immigrants from the soviet union israel 
radio reported 
israeli officials expect hundred of thousands of soviet 
immigrants over the next few years 
</TEXT>
