<TEXT>
david j whichard ii of the greenville nc 
daily reflector was elected to the board of directors of the 
associated press on monday and five incumbents were reelected 
james k batten j stewart bryan iii ruth s holmberg tom 
johnson and joe d smith jr were elected to new threeyear terms 
directors were elected from among 12 nominees at the aps annual 
meeting 
whichard was elected to the board to represent a city of under 
50000 population he succeeds retiring director john o emmerich 
jr of the greenwood miss commonwealth who was not eligible for 
reelection because he has served the maximum three consecutive 
threeyear terms 
batten is chairman and chief executive officer of knightridder 
inc based in miami 
bryan is chairman and publisher of the richmond va 
timesdispatch and the richmond news leader 
holmberg is publisher of the chattanooga tenn times 
johnson is chairman of the los angeles times 
smith is president of the alexandria la daily town talk 
the voting for directors was based on membership bonds held by 
the newspapers that make up the cooperative news agency 
the results 
batten 18495 bond votes 
johnson 14846 
smith 14814 
bryan 11599 
holmberg 11291 
robert h hartmann of the evansville ind press 8945 
george w wilson of the concord nh monitor 8563 
walter e bartlett of the greenville sc news 7329 
beverly kees of the fresno calif bee 5297 
richard l conner of the fort worth texas startelegram 2701 
in the separate contest for election to the board to represent a 
city of under 50000 population whichard received 11791 votes 
ted m natt of the longview wash daily news received 8739 votes 
</TEXT>
