king the troubled london musical about martin 
luther king jr opened monday to a fourminute standing ovation 
but poor reviews from the critics 
someone should put on a musical about the making of king it 
would probably turn out to be a good deal more entertaining than 
king itself charles spencer in the daily telegraph wrote the 
show bowed at the piccadilly theater after its original opening 
date april 4 was postponed three times 
maureen paton in the daily express wrote this treatment comes 
across as a simplified version for children it may be 
wellmeaning but its an insult to adults 
the show stars opera singers simon estes and cynthia haymon 
their strong singing deflected doubts about the absence of any 
insight into the private lives behind the public persona of the 
slain black civil rights leader and his wife coretta 
mondays premier brought to an end weeks of speculation about 
the show which for several weeks was making headlines almost daily 
as various directors and writers parted company with the project 
on march 6 coretta scott king announced in a statement that she 
was withdrawing her support because the show trivialized her 
husband she restored her support a week into previews 
the poet and lyricist maya angelou who withdrew at the same 
time as mrs king has yet to lend her support anew 
the finished product bears lyrics by both angelou and alistair 
beaton the briton who cowrote the 1988 london flop ziegfeld 
the director 39yearold clarke peters is a black american 
based in london who has the supporting role in the show as the 
garage mechanic george he was hired after gotz friedrich and 
graham vick two directors known for their work in opera quit the 
musical 
the book is billed as an adaptation by lonne elder iii an 
oscar nominee for the film sounder who followed fellow 
playwrights ron milner and richard nelson neither of whom receives 
credit in the program the sheer quantity of creative participants 
must account in part for the confused narrative and 
characterization of king 
spencer wrote in the daily telegraph it is sometimes hard to 
make out exactly what is going on still less where or when 
king is budgeted at 45 million and breaks even at close 
to 50 percent in the 1168seat theater according to producer 
hans flury 
the top ticket price of 41 puts king on financial par with 
londons reigning musical blockbusters miss saigon and the 
phantom of the opera 
