<TEXT>
christian shrines in the holy land will close 
friday and ring a funeral toll from their belltowers to protest a 
governmentfunded jewish settlement in the old citys christian 
quarter church leaders said 
the announcement came one day after the israeli government 
confirmed it put up 18 million to help finance the settlement of 
150 jews in a 72room complex near the church of the holy sepulcher 
in washington state department spokeswoman margaret tutwiler 
called the settler move into the christian quarter an insensitive 
and provocative action 
she said israels funding of the settlement is deeply 
disturbing and that us ambassador william brown was raising the 
issue with israeli officials 
in response foreign ministry spokesman yossi amihud said 
jerusalem is the sovereign capital of the state of israel and the 
government of israel will continue to stand by the rights of jews 
to settle in jerusalem 
in athens foreign minister antonis samaras summoned israels 
diplomatic representative moshe gilboa to protest the settlement 
government spokesman vyron polydoras said the settlement is in a 
compound owned by the greek orthodox church 
archbishop serapheim head of the greek orthodox church in 
greece also protested monday to israeli caretaker prime minister 
yitzhak shamir over the occupation 
the settlement set up april 11 has provoked angry 
demonstrations by christian clerics and palestinians both 
christian and moslem 
in announcing fridays daylong protest the leaders of 10 
christian sects in the holy land said government support for the 
settlement endangers the survival of all christian communities in 
the holy city 
we demand respect of the privileges and rights the christians 
have in the holy land greek orthodox patriarch diodorus i said 
on monday 
the settlement called neot david is the only jewish presence 
in the old citys christian sector its spokesmen have consistently 
said that no government money was involved in the settlement 
palestinian christians have complained that the settlement 
threatened the traditional separation of the christian moslem and 
jewish quarters of the old city 
the greek church which says a former tenant illegally leased 
the compound got an court order to have the jews evicted the 
supreme court will consider an appeal of the order on thursday 
fridays protest will mark the first time all christian holy 
places close said the rt rev samir kafiti anglican bishop of 
jerusalem the church leaders included roman catholic coptic and 
lutheran officials 
among the christian sites to be closed are jerusalems church of 
the holy sepulcher bethlehems church of the nativity and the 
church of the annunciation in nazareth 
israels religious affairs ministry said in a statement that the 
action gives rise to a suspicion that it might be an attempt to 
influence the supreme court which is hearing an appeal of an 
order to evict the jews 
the ministry also accused church leaders of a basic and 
serious violation of the statusquo of holy places that we try so 
much to preserve in order to allow an orderly religious worship 
jerusalem mayor teddy kollek said he was sorry the churches 
undertook drastic action before the legal process was completed 
but he condemned the damage to coexistence in the city and the 
standing of jerusalem caused by the settlers he said government 
support only deepens the doubts and sharpens the fears of the 
churches in jerusalem 
the governments acknowledgement sunday that it helped finance 
the settlement was the first confirmation of official involvement 
in buying arab property in jerusalems walled old city captured by 
israel in the 1967 middle east war 
it came as settlers prepared a new settlement in the occupied 
gaza strip and the government authorized the expansion of 
settlements in the occupied west bank 
the settlement activity follows the march 15 collapse of the 
coalition cabinet that left the government in the hands of shamir 
and his rightwing likud bloc which favors retaining the occupied 
territories 
shamir is leading the government on a caretaker basis while 
labor party leader shimon peres tries to form a government with 
ultraorthodox parties 
about 75000 jewish settlers live in the occupied lands home to 
17 million palestinians who have a rebellion for 28 months 
against israeli rule 
the christian leaders said the church will hold the protest 
regardless of the supreme court decision 
the church closure will be in effect between 9 am friday and 
an unspecified hour saturday church bells will toll on the hour 
from 9 am until noon friday 
diodorus i and kafiti said the closure may be longer than 
announced 
