<TEXT>
the gannett co inc blaming what it called the 
poorest advertising environment in almost 20 years reported a 
barely perceptible increase in firstquarter earnings april 17 
other quarterly reports showed lower earnings for the tribune 
co and media general inc and a 16 percent increase for ah belo 
corp of dallas 
gannett said earnings totaled 75 million or 47 cents a share 
in the quarter ended april 1 up slightly from 749 million or 47 
cents a share the prior year 
revenue slipped less than 1 percentage point to 8134 million 
from 8176 million a year earlier 
the company said newspaper advertising revenue declined by 3 
percent in the first quarter gannett said broadcast revenue also 
was lower but no figures were provided 
the tribune co of chicago blamed operating losses at the new 
york daily news and weakness in its newsprint business for a 9 
percent earnings drop 
the company had net income of 335 million or 43 cents a 
share in the three months ended april 1 down from 368 million 
or 49 cents a share a year earlier revenue rose 6 percent to 584 
million from 553 million in 1989s first quarter 
operating profit for the companys newspaper publishing group 
declined 10 percent to 557 million from 616 million 
the company attributed the decrease to larger operating losses 
at the daily news resulting from weaker market conditions and costs 
related to contract negotiations with the newspapers 10 unions 
operating profit improved for the rest of the newspaper group 
largely due to stronger chicago tribune results and lower newsprint 
costs the company said 
media general inc of richmond va reported lower revenues 
net income and earnings per share for the first quarter 
although 1990 revenue growth is expected the uncertainty of 
the economy currently is clouding the earnings outlook said 
james s evans the companys president and chief executive officer 
revenues declined to 148 million from 1493 million last year 
net income dropped sharply from 119 million or 46 cents a share 
in the first quarter of 1989 to 27 million or 10 cents a share 
this year 
first quarter 1989 net income included an aftertax gain of 57 
million or 22 cents a share from the sale of a california 
newsprint recycling mill 
excluding the 1989 onetime gain 1990 first quarter net income 
fell 563 percent 
media general said newspaper profits were 442 percent lower in 
the first quarter the company blamed the decline on faltering 
national retail and classified advertising sales 
media general is the parent of the richmond timesdispatch and 
the richmond news leader and other daily newspapers as well as 
several broadcast operations broadcast profits increased 25 
percent 
belo credited increased classified advertising and broadcast 
revenue for its earnings increase the company posted a profit of 
28 million or 14 cents a share in the first three months of the 
year compared with 24 million or 12 cents a share in the same 
period last year 
revenue rose to 563 million from 536 million reported in 
last years first quarter 
belo owns and operates the dallas morning news seven community 
newspapers in the dallasfort worth area and five televsion 
stations in several states 
