<TEXT>
prison journalist wilbert rideau recommended 
for parole again april 18 said he would be a free man had he spent 
his 29 years in the louisiana state penitentiary making license 
plates instead of running a newspaper 
rideau was convicted of killing a woman by cutting her throat 
and stabbing her in the heart 
ive tried to make amends the best i could in the only ways 
available to me ive done things that counted over the last 29 
years he said that was the only violent act of my life done 
when i was a wild teenager if i could change it i would 
on april 18 the louisiana pardon board recommended for the 
fourth time in six years that rideau be set free gov buddy roemer 
said he is inclined to reject the unanimous recommendation to 
commute rideaus life sentence a decision was not expected for at 
least a week 
rideau has been called a model inmate by prison authorities the 
editor of the prison magazine the angolite he also gives lectures 
to youth groups and gets out to go on national speaking tours on 
prison reform over the years he has had a literary agent and 
written freelance articles for up to four figures for publications 
such as penthouse 
rideau has won the robert f kennedy journalism award the 
american bar associations silver gavel award and the george polk 
award for special interest reporting 
the polk award came on two articles in the angolite prison a 
sexual jungle dealing with homosexual rape and the other side 
of murder which told of the aftermath of a killing 
the angolite which has carried stories on inmate suicides 
prison riots prisoner rights executions prison sports and 
special events was featured in the new york times sunday magazine 
and has been praised in time magazine the washington post and 
columbia journalism review 
rideau has appeared on national tv including abcs 
nightline on which he was on a fiveman panel with former 
chief justice warren e burger in a discussion of prison reform 
and that is why rideau thinks hes still in prison 
lets face it theyve released thousands of murderers since 
ive been in prison ive watched them come in and go out all 
anonymous he said 
the governor hasnt searched out the families of their victims 
to talk to theyve managed to get out because their greatest 
achievement as a prisoner was that they remained anonymous 
of the 31 prisoners sentenced to either death or life in prison 
sent to louisiana state penitentiary in 1962 only rideau remains 
behind bars 
its not like im asking for special treatment or 
consideration not when the system has released everybody else 
routinely convicted of the same or worse crimes the system exists 
for everybody else in the state but wilbert rideau he said 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
a lawyer for united press international told a 
federal appeals court april 18 it could go out of business if 
reuters is allowed to terminate a photo exchange agreement 
three judges of the 2nd us circuit court of appeals reserved 
decision on upis request for an injunction barring reuters from 
terminating the contract 
the judges however extended an earlier stay that keeps the 
agreement in effect until they issue a written decision 
the contract between the news services was made in 1984 and 
called for upi to supply reuters with pictures from the united 
states and for reuters to provide upi with pictures from other 
countries it was to run for 10 years beginning in 1985 
we will immediately lose customers the minute reuters cuts us 
off upi lawyer mitchell karlan told the court if we are 
unable to get pictures from reuters upi is going out of business 
upi is appealing a decision by us district judge peter k 
leisure that the agency had not shown it would be irreparably 
harmed if the arrangement was discontinued 
the injunction request stemmed from a counterclaim by upi to a 
reuters lawsuit that seeks to void the picture exchange agreement 
reuters said the agreement was not living up to expectations 
robert sugarman an attorney for reuters argued against the 
injunction on the grounds that upi had not shown how many customers 
it would lose without foreign photos from reuters 
sugarman pointed to testimony from upi chairman earl brian that 
upi had negotiated to receive foreign photos from the french news 
service agence francepresse for a threemonth period in the 
event the reuters contract is discontinued 
in a statement brian said we will continue to pursue upis 
rights by confronting reuters erratic and unwarranted behavior we 
take further encouragement from todays hearing and continuation of 
the order against reuters 
we at upi consider photos and graphics a strategically vital 
