<TEXT>
the san francisco chronicle has been named 
winner of the scripps howard foundation national journalism award 
for service to the first amendment 
the foundation on april 18 commended the newspaper and sunday 
punch section editor peter sussman for publishing the writings of a 
convictjournalist and then defending their right to do so 
inmate dannie martins writings led to the release of an 
unjustly sentenced man and a review of medical treatment received 
by convicts the judges noted 
the effort of the chronicle and sussman not only has helped 
illuminate the workings of americas prisons institutions often 
overlooked by the press it has emphasized the important principle 
that to deny an inmate the right to report about what he 
experiences is to violate the first amendment rights of all 
americans the judges said 
finalists included the kentucky post covington ky the 
milwaukee journal and the richmond va timesdispatch 
