<TEXT>
the supreme courts nine members are among the 
most private of public officials they wield enormous power but 
rarely hold news conferences or give interviews recent polls 
indicate only one in three americans can name any of the nine 
this the seventh in an occasional series offers an uptodate 
look at a member of the nations highest court 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
hes 84 now a passionate liberal on an 
increasingly conservative supreme court his health is not the 
best but william j brennan says he is having too much fun to 
retire 
im still enjoying myself nothing possibly could be as 
satisfying he told the associated press in an interview days 
before his 84th birthday wednesday 
ive been having some bad health of late i had that doggone 
attack in march that started i thought as influenza now 
thought to have been a more serious bronchial infection they gave 
me some antibiotics and i had a bad reaction lost a lot of 
weight brennan said they told me it might be as long as three 
months before i finally get fully recovered from it 
but retire if i can keep on the way i am im going to 
stay he said 
his stay to date has lasted 34 years and transcended the 
administrations of eight presidents 
in the courts history only one justice william o douglas 
wrote more opinions only three court members served at more 
advanced ages oliver wendell holmes at 91 roger taney at 87 and 
hugo black at 85 
few have written with such literary grace and eloquence 
appointed by president dwight d eisenhower brennan helped lead 
a liberal revolution in american law through the 1960s the 
protection of individual rights was elevated to new heights 
some called brennan an ideologue and an activist some called 
him a champion of the underdog 
in a 1987 law school speech he said when i think of the 
progress we have made over the last 30 years i look upon our 
system of civil liberties with some satisfaction and a certain 
pride 
gradually his role changed ronald reagans legacy three key 
court appointments has left brennan often outmanned in his fight 
against a nascent conservative counterrevolution 
in recent years the other side has pretty much carried the 
day brennan said that strikes me as nothing to be surprised 
about after all the president fills the vacancies 
in a recent interview published in new yorker magazine brennan 
was quoted as saying im not discouraged to the point of giving 
up i hope people dont overdo the suggestion that were headed for 
perdition 
he added im not going to walk out and say the hell with it 
even in recent years brennan has registered major successes 
some of them prompted daniel popeo of the conservative washington 
legal foundation to state unfortunately i think the man is 
extremely intelligent hes been a key player now under three chief 
justices he deserves professional respect 
brennan told ap of one possible exception to his resolve against 
retirement if the good lord steps in and something happens that 
i wouldnt be able to carry on 
i have a pledge from my wife that the day she notices it 
shell tell me so ill act accordingly he said i think it 
would be so wrong to stay here unless youre fully able to do your 
job too much rides on what we do around here 
among the more than 1200 opinions written by brennan are 
landmarks that imposed a one person one vote standard for 
electing state legislatures created constitutional protections for 
libel lawsuit defendants and helped invent a legal definition of 
obscenity 
new york university law professor burt neuborne evaluating 
brennans opinions and his contribution to the justices 
deliberations once called him the most influential supreme court 
member since john marshall the great chief justice of the early 
19th century 
the comment makes brennan wince 
honestly thats so overstated so overdrawn even the greats 
of the past holmes brandeis theyd never stand for such a 
claim he said 
but retired justice lewis f powell for 15 years brennans 
colleague said in a recent interview i have no doubt he will 
have a high ranking among the courts members bill is one of 
historys great justices 
although far more conservative than brennan in his judicial 
views powell said their professional differences never impaired 
our friendship he is a man of great personal warmth 
reminded of his reputation as a skilled behindthescenes 
coalition builder brennan took exception i dont know who 
invented that you know damn well its not true he said you 
do your best and as often as not when you end up with a majority 
it reflects many ideas of your colleagues and not only yours 
he said the courts members persuade each other in written 
memos not in backroom deals or smokefilled meetings 
a sample of brennans writing style and perhaps his power of 
persuasion was displayed in a speech he wrote to celebrate the 
constitutions 200th birthday 
our entire constitution is a national treasure a document of 
heady ideals and eloquent elegant language a political landmark 
for individual rights he wrote 
but one thing the old parchment is not is a china doll that 
has to be protected from the regular world by a good layer of 
cotton wool it is a tough old soldier thats collected quite a few 
respectable dents in the line of duty 
</TEXT>
