oregon has released prisoners early for years the state also 
has a rotating bunk system whereby an inmate is released for seven 
days while another takes his bunk when the first inmate returns 
someone else is released for a week 
in april 1989 the georgia board of pardons and paroles began an 
emergency early release of 3000 prisoners to avert a threatened 
