27518 for the former and 30403 for the latter salaries are 
highest in the northeast and lowest in the southwest and midwest 
skelton says that the demand may even be higher than the survey 
shows we polled only established consulting firms that have 
already carved out their stable share of the market and we know we 
are missing the many new firms entering the field of waste 
management and environmental engineering 
another field with shortages is nuclear pharmacy for dealing 
with radiopharmaceuticals and radioactive drugs used in diagnosing 
diseases like heart conditions and cancer 
limited resources and a lack of qualified teachers have made it 
difficult to start programs in this specialty says stan shaw 
professor of nuclear pharmacy at purdue university in west 
lafayette ind other schools with programs are massachusetts 
college of pharmacy mercer school of pharmacy temple university 
university of kentucky and university of new mexico 
if the student can make it through the college program and has 
genuine interest in nuclear pharmacy he or she should have no 
problem finding a job says steve piepenbrink a nuclear 
pharmacist at syncor international co in indianapolis at 
syncor there are at least 20 positions open throughout the company 
on an ongoing basis a problem faced by nuclear pharmacies 
nationwide 
these drugs are only occasionally used for therapy he says the 
primary use is diagnostic usually the drug is injected 
intravenously into the patient and absorbed into the organ or 
tissue under observation radioactive atoms decay and emit 
radiation that is detected by a gamma camera the drug will appear 
as excessive or small amounts of radioactivity in the tissue or 
organ alerting a doctor to the possibility of disease 
the field will continue to grow says shaw there are many new 
radiopharmaceuticals for diagnosis and therapy being developed and 
there will be a bigger challenge to develop resources needed to 
educate students 
