the poison pill and confidential voting proposals had no comment 
on the bass group disclosure 
a poison pill defense makes it prohibitively expensive to take 
over a company keeping the identity of those voting in shareholder 
elections secret from management has been a growing issue among 
shareholders rights groups 
the bass group announcement came three weeks after avons 
largest shareholder chartwell associates said it had boosted its 
stake to 16 percent chartwell had been pressuring avon management 
for representation on the board 
