initiated by american express 
american express lost 620 million in the first three months of 
1990 because of the troubles at shearson 
its the price we paid to put shearsons major problems behind 
us robinson told about 500 shareholders attending american 
express annual meeting in new york 
shearson needed time and capital but market conditions 
demanded immediate action he said 
american express last month announced a plan to buy all the 
remaining publicly held shares of shearson capping several months 
of turmoil at the wall street firm that analysts say overexpanded 
in the 1980s 
the payment card and travel services giant moved to gain 
management control of shearson by ousting peter cohen as chairman 
and installing an american express executive in his place howard 
l clark jr 
shearson then laid off 2000 workers in march with more 
expected by the end of the year and began plans to eliminate or 
scale back several business lines 
in addition to extending its current 61 percent stake to full 
ownership american express has provided 115 billion to shore up 
shearsons capital base in recent months 
robinson said that six months ago shearson didnt fit as a 
core operating entity and had been reduced to a strategic 
investment 
he attributed shearsons troubles to declining stock trading 
activity since the 1987 market crash rising worldwide interest 
rates a slumping domestic real estate market and the collapse of 
the junk bond market last fall 
the environment for securities companies changed rapidly and 
radically robinson said the result was a crisis for 
shearson 
but he said american express changes at the investment firm had 
left shearson well positioned to make money he did not say 
when he expected shearson to become profitable 
robinson admitted that some of shearsons expansion moves in the 
1980s under cohen were wrong including the 1988 purchase of ef 
hutton inc which added an extensive retail brokerage network and 
expensive overhead while causing animosity among employees 
in retrospect the hutton acquisition or at least the way it 
was structured was a mistake he said 
at the annual meeting shareholders elected three new american 
